üß™ LAB PART (VERY IMPORTANT ‚Äì PRACTICAL + VIVA)
üîπ LAB 1: Create Self-Signed Certificate using OpenSSL
openssl genrsa -out server.key 2048
openssl req -new -key server.key -out server.csr
openssl x509 -req -days 365 -in server.csr -signkey server.key -out server.crt
üîπ LAB 2: Setup Hierarchical PKI using OpenSSL
üü† Root CA (rtca.pgditiss.local ‚Äì Debian)
Generate Root CA private key
Create Root CA certificate (self-signed)
üü† Sub CA (sbca.pgditiss.local ‚Äì Debian)
Generate Sub CA key
Create CSR
Root CA signs Sub CA certificate
üîπ LAB 3: Issue Website Certificate
Domain: www.pgditiss.local

Steps:

Generate website key
Create CSR (CN = www.pgditiss.local)
Sub CA signs CSR
Certificate issued by Sub CA
üîπ LAB 4: Configure HTTPS on Apache
Install Apache

Configure:

Server certificate
Private key
CA chain file
Access:
üëâ https://www.pgditiss.local

üîπ LAB 5: DNS / Name Resolution
Configure /etc/hosts or DNS entry
Map:
www.pgditiss.local ‚Üí Server IP
üéØ CCEE QUICK REVISION (SESSION 13)
SSL ‚Üí deprecated, TLS ‚Üí secure
